track_notes: From the car park area at NZ 022075. We went through the wood to the Kettle Stone first to see it but then activated from inside the sink hole near to the trig point NZ 004073. If you decided to operate from near to the Kettle Stone or the Frying Pan Stone this is just within the AZ. There is a fence there that would support your pole.

From the parking spot at the signposts for Welcome to Teesdale/County Durham Border its not a long walk but is it boggy. Even Hurr Gill which was almost dry presented a problem trying to find somewhere to cross. I got to the Trig point eventually but not without going ankle deep on more than one occasion.
